                  </linearGradient>
                </defs>
                <path fill="url(#half-star-blue)" d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#1a1a1a] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            "This learning experience strengthened my understanding of Agile and how to use Jira as a practical decision-making tool, not just a task tracker. I now have clearer criteria to structure workflows, choose between Scrum and Kanban, and use metrics to improve visibility and flow. Special thanks to Danny Liu for such a clear, direct, and practical approach—focused on what truly matters to achieve the objective."
          </p>
          <p class="font-bold text-[#1a1a1a]">Victor Emilio Moreno Leon</p>
